^ABSPF(9002313.94,0)="ABSP INSURANCE RULES^9002313.94^6^6"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,1,0)="WORKERS COMP RULE^WORKCOMP~ABSPOS26"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,1,1,0)="^^5^5^3010612^^"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,1,1,1,0)="Visits may be marked as work-related (V POV file has data)."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,1,1,2,0)="Insurers may be marked as worker's comp only, never, or both worker's comp"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,1,1,3,0)="and non-worker's comp claims (ABSP INSURER file has data)."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,1,1,4,0)="This rule takes these settings into consideration and adjusts"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,1,1,5,0)="the order of insurance accordingly."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,0)="EMPLOYMENT BEFORE PRIVATE INS^NULL~ABSPOS26"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,0)="^^12^12^3010612^^"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,1,0)="This rule has no effect.  It relies on the EMPLOYER field of the POLICY"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,2,0)="HOLDER file which is pointed to by the PRIVATE INSURANCE ELIGIBLE file."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,3,0)="Unfortunately, it turns out that this EMPLOYER field is not available"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,4,0)="when the patient is the policy holder.  The rule may be selected and"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,5,0)="assigned a point value but it will not affect the order of insurance"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,6,0)="computations.  The intent of the rule was as follows:"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,7,0)="If insurance through employment takes precendence over"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,8,0)="insurance through private purchase, use this rule."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,9,0)="Note that the policy holder employer in the private insurance page"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,10,0)="must be filled in - that's how the rule knows that insurance"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,11,0)="is through employment.  Other employment data in registration"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,2,1,12,0)="doesn't suffice for this rule's needs."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,0)="EMPLOYMENT BEFORE SPOUSE INS^NULL~ABSPOS26"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,0)="^^11^11^3010612^^"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,1,0)="This rule has no effect.  See the explanation under the EMPLOYMENT BEFORE"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,2,0)="PRIVATE INS rule for technical details of why this is so.  This rule may"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,3,0)="be selected and assigned a point value but it will have no effect on the "
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,4,0)="computation of the order of insurance.  The recommended workaround"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,5,0)="is to use the POLICY HOLDER IS SELF rule; this will take care of "
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,6,0)="most cases. "
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,7,0)="The intent of the original rule was as follows:"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,8,0)="If insurance through your employment is to take precendence over"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,9,0)="insurance under a spouse's employment coverage, then use this rule."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,10,0)="The relationship to policyholder (SELF) and the policy holder employer"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,3,1,11,0)="are important to making this rule work as intended."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,0)="BIRTHDAY RULE (2 PARENTS)^BIRTHDAY~ABSPOS26"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,0)="^^7^7^3000818^"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,1,0)="If a child is covered by policies from two parents' employment,"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,2,0)="the policy through the parent whose birthday comes first in the calendar"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,3,0)="year is the one that takes precedence.  This rule figures it out."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,4,0)="The relationship to policyholder, the policy holder emloyer,"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,5,0)="and the policy holder date of birth are critical to making this rule"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,6,0)="work as intended.  If a policy holder date of birth is missing,"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,4,1,7,0)="a midyear date will be used."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,5,0)="SEARHC SPECIAL RULE 0^SEARHC0~ABSPOS26"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,5,1,0)="^^2^2^3000818^"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,5,1,1,0)="Special for SEARHC - Medicare, Native beneficiary, Private insurance too -"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,5,1,2,0)="this constitutes a special case, handled by SEARHC SPECIAL RULE 0."
^ABSPF(9002313.94,6,0)="POLICY HOLDER IS SELF^SELFRULE~ABSPOS26"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,6,1,0)="^^2^2^3010612^^"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,6,1,1,0)="This rule is used to assign bonus points to policies where"
^ABSPF(9002313.94,6,1,2,0)="the policy holder is SELF.  "
